{"title_page": "Pak Jong-nam", "text_new": "{{Infobox officeholder\n|name         =  Pak Jong-nam\n|native_name  = \ubc15\uc815\ub0a8\n|image        = \n|office       = Chairman of the WPK Kangwon Provincial Committee\n|1blankname   = {{nowrap|[[Supreme Leader of North Korea|Supreme Leader]]}}\n|1namedata    = [[Kim Jong-un]]\n|president    = \n|term_start   = 2017\n|term_end     = \n|predecessor  = \n|successor    = \n|office1      = \n|president1    = \n|term_start1   = \n|term_end1     = \n|predecessor1  = \n|successor1    = \n|birth_date   = \n|birth_place  = \n|death_date   = \n|death_place  = \n|party        = [[Workers' Party of Korea]]\n}}\n'''Pak Jong-nam ({{lang-ko|\ubc15\uc815\ub0a8}})''' is a [[North Korea]]n politician. He is a member of the [[Politburo of the Workers' Party of Korea|Political Bureau]] of the [[Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea|Central Committee]] of the [[Workers' Party of Korea]] and Chairman of the [[Kangwon Province (North Korea)|Kangwon Province]] Provincial Party Committee.\n\n==Biography==\nIn March 1996, he took over as the WPK Commitee of [[Hamhung]], and in July 2001 was appointed secretary of [[Kangwon Province (North Korea)|Kangwon Province]] WPK Committee.<ref>[https://www.nocutnews.co.kr/news/4591096 \u201c\u5317, \ub2f9 \uc911\uc559\uc704\uc6d0 128\uba85, \ud6c4\ubcf4\uc704\uc6d0 106\uba85 \ubc1c\ud45c\u201d. \u300a\ub178\ucef7\ub274\uc2a4\u300b. 2016\ub144 5\uc6d4 10\uc77c. 2018\ub144 8\uc6d4 31\uc77c\uc5d0 \ud655\uc778\ud568.]</ref> In May 2013, he became the party secretary in [[Kangwon Province (North Korea)|Kangwon Province]] succeeding . In May 2016, he was appointed a member of the Central Committee of the Workers 'Party at the 7th Congress of the Workers' Party.<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20180831104249/https://nocutnews.co.kr/news/4593604# \u201c\u5317 \uc2dc\u00b7\ub3c4 \ub2f9 \ucc45\uc784\ube44\uc11c, \uc2dc\u00b7\ub3c4 \ub2f9 \uc704\uc6d0\uc7a5\uc73c\ub85c \ubcc0\uacbd\u201d. \u300a\ub178\ucef7\ub274\uc2a4\u300b. 2016\ub144 5\uc6d4 16\uc77c. 2018\ub144 8\uc6d4 31\uc77c\uc5d0 \uc6d0\ubcf8 \ubb38\uc11c\uc5d0\uc11c \ubcf4\uc874\ub41c \ubb38\uc11c. 2018\ub144 8\uc6d4 31\uc77c\uc5d0 \ud655\uc778\ud568]</ref> In June 2016 he was elected chairman of the Party Committee of [[Kangwon Province (North Korea)|Kangwon Province]].\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Workers' Party of Korea politicians]]\n", "text_old": "'''Pak Jong-nam ({{lang-ko|\ubc15\uc815\ub0a8}})''' is a [[North Korea]]n politician. He is a member of the [[Politburo of the Workers' Party of Korea|Political Bureau]] of the [[Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea|Central Committee]] of the [[Workers' Party of Korea]] and Chairman of the [[Kangwon Province (North Korea)|Kangwon Province]] Provincial Party Committee.\n\n==Biography==\nIn March 1996, he took over as the WPK Commitee of [[Hamhung]], and in July 2001 was appointed secretary of [[Kangwon Province (North Korea)|Kangwon Province]] WPK Committee.<ref>[https://www.nocutnews.co.kr/news/4591096 \u201c\u5317, \ub2f9 \uc911\uc559\uc704\uc6d0 128\uba85, \ud6c4\ubcf4\uc704\uc6d0 106\uba85 \ubc1c\ud45c\u201d. \u300a\ub178\ucef7\ub274\uc2a4\u300b. 2016\ub144 5\uc6d4 10\uc77c. 2018\ub144 8\uc6d4 31\uc77c\uc5d0 \ud655\uc778\ud568.]</ref> In May 2013, he became the party secretary in [[Kangwon Province (North Korea)|Kangwon Province]] succeeding . In May 2016, he was appointed a member of the Central Committee of the Workers 'Party at the 7th Congress of the Workers' Party.<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20180831104249/https://nocutnews.co.kr/news/4593604# \u201c\u5317 \uc2dc\u00b7\ub3c4 \ub2f9 \ucc45\uc784\ube44\uc11c, \uc2dc\u00b7\ub3c4 \ub2f9 \uc704\uc6d0\uc7a5\uc73c\ub85c \ubcc0\uacbd\u201d. \u300a\ub178\ucef7\ub274\uc2a4\u300b. 2016\ub144 5\uc6d4 16\uc77c. 2018\ub144 8\uc6d4 31\uc77c\uc5d0 \uc6d0\ubcf8 \ubb38\uc11c\uc5d0\uc11c \ubcf4\uc874\ub41c \ubb38\uc11c. 2018\ub144 8\uc6d4 31\uc77c\uc5d0 \ud655\uc778\ud568]</ref> In June 2016 he was elected chairman of the Party Committee of [[Kangwon Province (North Korea)|Kangwon Province]].\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Workers' Party of Korea politicians]]\n", "name_user": "Rakoon", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pak_Jong-nam"}
{"title_page": "Helena Deland", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2019}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name             = \n| image            = Helena Deland Summit Music Hall 03.19.10 (40465729803) (cropped).jpg\n| image_upright    = \n| image_size       = \n| landscape        = <!-- yes, if wide image, otherwise leave blank -->\n| alt              = \n| caption          = Deland performing in 2019\n| background       = solo_singer\n| birth_name       = \n| alias            = \n| birth_date       = <!-- {{Birth date and age|df=yes|YYYY|MM|DD}} -->\n| birth_place      = [[Vancouver]], [[British Columbia]]\n| origin           = \n| death_date       = <!-- {{Death date and age|df=yes|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} (death date first) -->\n| death_place      = \n| genre            = \n| occupation       = \n| instrument       = {{hlist|Vocals|guitar|piano}}\n| years_active     = \n| label            = Luminelle Recordings\n| associated_acts  = \n| website          = {{URL|helenadeland.com}}\n| module           = \n| module2          = \n| module3          = \n}}\n\n'''Helena Deland''' is a Canadian songwriter, composer, singer and musician. To date she has released five [[Extended play|EPs]]: ''Drawing Room'' (2016<ref name=\"stereogum\">{{cite web |last1=Robinson |first1=Collin |title=Helena Deland \u2013 \"Aix\" |url=https://www.stereogum.com/1891909/helena-deland-aix/mp3s/ |publisher=[[Stereogum]] |accessdate=12 November 2018}}</ref>) and ''From the Series of Songs \"Altogether Unaccompanied\"'' Vol. I, II, III & IV (2018) that she has written and composed. Helena Deland is currently signed to Luminelle Recordings (label founded by [[Gorilla vs. Bear]] & [[Fat Possum Records]]) for the world as well as Chivi Chivi for Canada. She has toured consistently since the beginning of her career in [[Canada]], [[United States]] and [[Europe]].\n\n==Biography==\nBorn in [[Vancouver]], [[British Columbia]], Deland grew up in Quebec City and currently lives in [[Montreal]]. Her native languages are French and English; however, she primarily writes and sings in English.<ref>Werner, Mackenzie. [http://www.hooliganmagazine.com/blog/2018/12/15/interview-a-conversation-with-helena-deland \"INTERVIEW: A conversation with Helena Deland\"], ''[[Hooligan Magazine]]'', 15 December 2018. Retrieved on 6 March 2019.</ref> She began playing piano and guitar as a child and started singing when she moved to Montreal.<ref>Kidwell, Zoe. [https://milk.xyz/articles/getting-personal-with-helena-deland/ \"Getting personal with Helena Deland\"], [[Milk]], 19 October 2018. Retrieved on 6 March 2019.</ref> Helena Deland's inspirations are diverse:<ref>Finn, Rachel. [http://diymag.com/2018/08/28/get-to-know-helena-deland-interview/ \"Get to know\u2026 Helena Deland\"], [[DIY Mag]], 28 August 2018. Retrieved on 6 March 2019.</ref>  [[Jessica Pratt (musician)|Jessica Pratt]], [[Joni Mitchell]], Sea Oleena.\n\n==Discography==\n\n'''2018:''' '''''From the Series of Songs \"Altogether Unaccompanied\"''''' '''Vol. I & II,<ref>Lu, Leah. [https://uproxx.com/music/helena-deland-ep-stream/  \"Stream Helena Deland\u2019s entrancing new EP, \u2018From The Series of Songs \u2018Altogether Unaccompanied\u2019 Vol. I & II\u2019\"], [[Uproxx]], 3 March 2018. Retrieved on 5 March 2019.</ref> III & IV'''<ref>Hmood, Zahraa. [https://exclaim.ca/music/article/helena_deland-altogether_unaccompanied_vol_iii_and_iv \"Helena Deland, Altogether Unaccompanied Vol. III & IV \"], ''[[Exclaim!]]'', 16 October 2018. Retrieved on 5 March 2019.</ref><ref>Leli\u00e8vre, Nathan. [https://www.icimusique.ca/albumsenecoute/911/helena-deland-altogether-unaccompanied-iii-iv  \"Helena Deland: vive, intime et singuli\u00e8re sur Altogether Unaccompanied Vol. III & IV \"], [[Ici Musique]], 19 October 2018. Retrieved on 5 March 2019.</ref>\n\nThis series of four volumes, produced by [[Secret City Records|Jesse Mac Cormack]],<ref>Editorial Staff. [https://www.cbcmusic.ca/posts/20666/the-10-best-new-canadian-artists-of-2018 \"10 new Canadian artists that ruled 2018\"], [[CBC Music]], 7 December 2018. Retrieved on 6 March 2019.</ref> was meant to be released as a complete album. The songs were so varied in genre that it was decided to release them separately with the objective of gathering songs that were similar in their themes and sounds.<ref>Powell, Aaron. [https://www.thelineofbestfit.com/features/interviews/on-the-rise-helena-deland-interview-2018 \"On The Rise: Helena Deland\"], [[The Line Of Best Fit]], 9 October 2018. Retrieved on 6 March 2019.</ref><ref>Lindsay, Cam. [https://exclaim.ca/music/article/helena_deland_discusses_montreal_community_gorilla_vs_bear_and_making_day_music_or_night_music \" Helena Deland Discusses Montreal Community, Gorilla Vs. Bear and Making Day Music or Night Music\"], [[Exclaim!]], 18 October 2018. Retrieved on 6 March 2019.</ref> Helena Deland inspirations have a common theme: human relationships.<ref>Lu, Leah. [https://uproxx.com/music/helena-deland-interview-altogether-unaccompanied-volumes-3-4/\" Canadian Songwriter Helena Deland On The Friendships That Inspire Her Meditative Synth-Pop\"], [[Uproxx]], 17 October 2018. Retrieved on 6 March 2019.</ref>\n\nVol. I & II were released on 2 March and Vol. III & IV were released on 19 October 2018 via Luminelle Recordings and Chivi Chivi.\n\n{{Track listing\n| headline      = Vol. I\n\n|all_writing = Helena Deland\n\n| title_width   = 70%\n| writing_width = \n| music_width   = \n| lyrics_width  =  \n| extra_width   = \n| title1        = There Are a Thousand<ref>Johnson, Tom. [https://www.goldflakepaint.co.uk/new-music-helena-deland-there-are-a-thousand/  \"Helena Deland, There Are a Thousand\"], [[Gold Flake Paint]], 2018. Retrieved on 5 March 2019.</ref>\n| length1       = 3:36\n\n| title2        = Perfect Weather for a Crime<ref>Jett\u00e9, Elise. [https://www.journaldemontreal.com/25-chansons-queb-qui-ont-marque-2018 \"25 chansons queb qui ont marqu\u00e9 2018\"], [[Journal de Montr\u00e9al]], 27 December 2018. Retrieved on 5 March 2019.</ref> \n|length2       = 2:24\n}}\n{{Track listing\n| headline      = Vol. II\n| total_length  = 14:54\n\n| title_width   = 70%\n| writing_width = \n| music_width   = \n| lyrics_width  =  \n| extra_width   =\n\n| title1        = Take It All<ref>MacDonald, Sarah. [https://noisey.vice.com/en_ca/article/a343az/helena-delands-take-it-all-tackles-the-reality-of-romantic-expectations \"Helena Deland's \"Take It All\"], [[Noisey]], 15 February 2018. Retrieved on 5 March 2019.</ref>\n| length1       = 4:36\n\n| title2        = Body Language<ref>Israelsohn, Sophie. [https://www.stereogum.com/1985086/stream-helena-deland-from-the-series-of-songs-altogether-unaccompanied-vol-i-ii/music/album-stream/ \"Stream Helena Deland From The Series Of Songs \"Altogether Unaccompanied\" Vol. I & II\"], [[Stereogum]], 1 March 2018. Retrieved on 5 March 2019.</ref> \n| length2       = 4:18\n}}\n{{Track listing\n| headline      = Vol. III\n\n| title_width   = 70%\n| writing_width = \n| music_width   = \n| lyrics_width  =  \n| extra_width   =\n\n| title1        = Two Queries<ref>Murphy, Sarah. [https://exclaim.ca/music/article/helena_deland_teases_two_new_eps_with_claudion \"Helena Deland teases two new EPs with \u2018Claudion\u2019 \"], [[Exclaim!]], 25 July 2018. Retrieved on 5 March 2019.</ref>\n| length1       = 1:43\n\n| title2        = A Stone is a Stone<ref>Pareles Jon, Caramanica Jon and Russonello Giovanni. [https://www.nytimes.com/2018/10/26/arts/music/playlist-cardi-b-lauren-jauregui-xxxtentacion-lil-pump.html?emc=edit_ms_20181026&nl=louder&nlid=8666185820181026&te=1 \"The Playlist: Cardi B Hits Pay Dirt, and 11 Mor New Songs \"], [[New York Times]], 26 October 2018. Retrieved on 5 March 2019.</ref>\n| length2       = 4:13\n\n| title3        = Lean on You<ref>Gordon, Holly. [https://www.cbcmusic.ca/posts/20414/premiere-listen-montreal-helena-deland-lean-on-you \"Premiere: listen to Helena Deland\u2019s hypnotic new song \u2018Lean on You\u2019 \"], [[CBC Music]], 19 September 2018. Retrieved on 5 March 2019.</ref>\n| length3       = 5:12}}\n{{Track listing\n| headline      = Vol. IV\n| total_length  = 18:16\n\n| title_width   = 70%\n| writing_width = \n| music_width   = \n| lyrics_width  =  \n| extra_width   =\n\n| title1        = Claudion<ref>Wang, Steffanee. [http://www.thefader.com/2018/07/25/helena-deland-claudion-altogether-unaccompanied  \" Helena Deland\u2019s \"Claudion\" will make you love synth-pop\"], [[The Fader]], 25 July 2018. Retrieved on 5 March 2019.</ref>\n| length1       = 4:28\n\n| title2        = Rise<ref>Powell, Aaron. [https://www.thelineofbestfit.com/new-music/song-of-the-day/helena-deland-rise \" Helena Deland shares hypnotic ballad \"Rise\" \"], [[The Line of Best Fit]], 22 August 2018. Retrieved on 5 March 2019.</ref>\n| length2       = 3:40\n}}\n\n'''2016:''' '''''Drawing Room'''''\n\n''Drawing Room'' is Helena Deland's first [[Extended play|EP]] released on 26 August 2016 under Montreal label Chivi Chivi. Produced by Jesse Mac Cormack, it includes four songs written and composed by Helena.\n\n{{Track listing\n| headline      = \n| total_length  = 16:38\n\n| title_width   = 70%\n| writing_width = \n| music_width   = \n| lyrics_width  =  \n| extra_width   =\n\n| title1        = Aix<ref>Spill New Music. [http://spillmagazine.com/spill-music-premiere-helena-deland-aix/ \"Spill Music Premier: Helena Deland \u2013 \u2018Aix\u2019 \"], [[Spill Magazine]], 26 August 2016. Retrieved on 5 March 2019.</ref>\n| length1       = 4:12\n\n| title2        = Black Metal<ref>Th\u00e9rien, Val\u00e9rie. [https://voir.ca/nouvelles/actualite-musicale/2016/08/19/ecoute-integrale-helena-deland-drawing-room-ep/ \"Ecoute int\u00e9grale : Helena Deland Drawing Room (EP) \"], [[Voir (journal)]], 19 August 2016. Retrieved on 5 March 2019.</ref>\n|length2       = 3:42\n\n| title3        = Baby\n|length3       = 4:29\n\n| title4        = Drawing Room<ref>Rayner, Ben. [https://www.thestar.com/e