-deland-altogether-unaccompanied-vol-iii-iv \"First Play Live: Helena Deland, From the Series of Songs \u201cAltogether Unaccompanied\u201d Vol. III & IV\"], [[CBC Music]], 15 October 2018. Retrieved on 5 March 2019.</ref> ([https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=l4VY--K2BOA Rise], [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ilT6NuWVFJ8 Baby], [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=IL36Xd6z6CA A Stone is a Stone], [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=z8_RXv3lUwg Body Language], [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E1kI9fkLzMk Take It All],  | First Play Live)\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Deland, Helena}}\n[[Category:Canadian female singers]]\n[[Category:Canadian songwriters]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Musicians from Montreal]]\n[[Category:Musicians from Quebec City]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2019}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name             = \n| image            = Helena Deland Summit Music Hall 03.19.10 (40465729803) (cropped).jpg\n| image_upright    = \n| image_size       = \n| landscape        = <!-- yes, if wide image, otherwise leave blank -->\n| alt              = \n| caption          = Deland performing in 2019\n| background       = solo_singer\n| birth_name       = \n| alias            = \n| birth_date       = <!-- {{Birth date and age|df=yes|YYYY|MM|DD}} -->\n| birth_place      = [[Vancouver]], [[British Columbia]]\n| origin           = \n| death_date       = <!-- {{Death date and age|df=yes|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} (death date first) -->\n| death_place      = \n| genre            = \n| occupation       = \n| instrument       = {{hlist|Vocals|guitar|piano}}\n| years_active     = \n| label            = Luminelle Recordings\n| associated_acts  = \n| website          = {{URL|helenadeland.com}}\n| module           = \n| module2          = \n| module3          = \n}}\n\n'''Helena Deland''' is a Canadian songwriter, composer, singer and musician. To date she has released five [[Extended play|EPs]]: ''Drawing Room'' (2016<ref name=\"stereogum\">{{cite web |last1=Robinson |first1=Collin |title=Helena Deland \u2013 \"Aix\" |url=https://www.stereogum.com/1891909/helena-deland-aix/mp3s/ |publisher=[[Stereogum]] |accessdate=12 November 2018}}</ref>) and ''From the Series of Songs \"Altogether Unaccompanied\"'' Vol. I, II, III & IV (2018) that she has written and composed. Helena Deland is currently signed to Luminelle Recordings (label founded by [[Gorilla vs. Bear]] & [[Fat Possum Records]]) for the world as well as Chivi Chivi for Canada. She has toured consistently since the beginning of her career in [[Canada]], [[United States]] and [[Europe]].\n\n==Biography==\nBorn in [[Vancouver]], [[British Columbia]], Deland grew up in Quebec City and currently lives in [[Montreal]]. Her native languages are French and English; however, she primarily writes and sings in English.<ref>Werner, Mackenzie. [http://www.hooliganmagazine.com/blog/2018/12/15/interview-a-conversation-with-helena-deland \"INTERVIEW: A conversation with Helena Deland\"], ''[[Hooligan Magazine]]'', 15 December 2018. Retrieved on 6 March 2019.</ref> She began playing piano and guitar as a child and started singing when she moved to Montreal.<ref>Kidwell, Zoe. [https://milk.xyz/articles/getting-personal-with-helena-deland/ \"Getting personal with Helena Deland\"], [[Milk]], 19 October 2018. Retrieved on 6 March 2019.</ref> Helena Deland's inspirations are diverse:<ref>Finn, Rachel. [http://diymag.com/2018/08/28/get-to-know-helena-deland-interview/ \"Get to know\u2026 Helena Deland\"], [[DIY Mag]], 28 August 2018. Retrieved on 6 March 2019.</ref>  [[Jessica Pratt]], [[Joni Mitchell]], Sea Oleena.\n\n==Discography==\n\n'''2018:''' '''''From the Series of Songs \"Altogether Unaccompanied\"''''' '''Vol. I & II,<ref>Lu, Leah. [https://uproxx.com/music/helena-deland-ep-stream/  \"Stream Helena Deland\u2019s entrancing new EP, \u2018From The Series of Songs \u2018Altogether Unaccompanied\u2019 Vol. I & II\u2019\"], [[Uproxx]], 3 March 2018. Retrieved on 5 March 2019.</ref> III & IV'''<ref>Hmood, Zahraa. [https://exclaim.ca/music/article/helena_deland-altogether_unaccompanied_vol_iii_and_iv \"Helena Deland, Altogether Unaccompanied Vol. III & IV \"], ''[[Exclaim!]]'', 16 October 2018. Retrieved on 5 March 2019.</ref><ref>Leli\u00e8vre, Nathan. [https://www.icimusique.ca/albumsenecoute/911/helena-deland-altogether-unaccompanied-iii-iv  \"Helena Deland: vive, intime et singuli\u00e8re sur Altogether Unaccompanied Vol. III & IV \"], [[Ici Musique]], 19 October 2018. Retrieved on 5 March 2019.</ref>\n\nThis series of four volumes, produced by [[Secret City Records|Jesse Mac Cormack]],<ref>Editorial Staff. [https://www.cbcmusic.ca/posts/20666/the-10-best-new-canadian-artists-of-2018 \"10 new Canadian artists that ruled 2018\"], [[CBC Music]], 7 December 2018. Retrieved on 6 March 2019.</ref> was meant to be released as a complete album. The songs were so varied in genre that it was decided to release them separately with the objective of gathering songs that were similar in their themes and sounds.<ref>Powell, Aaron. [https://www.thelineofbestfit.com/features/interviews/on-the-rise-helena-deland-interview-2018 \"On The Rise: Helena Deland\"], [[The Line Of Best Fit]], 9 October 2018. Retrieved on 6 March 2019.</ref><ref>Lindsay, Cam. [https://exclaim.ca/music/article/helena_deland_discusses_montreal_community_gorilla_vs_bear_and_making_day_music_or_night_music \" Helena Deland Discusses Montreal Community, Gorilla Vs. Bear and Making Day Music or Night Music\"], [[Exclaim!]], 18 October 2018. Retrieved on 6 March 2019.</ref> Helena Deland inspirations have a common theme: human relationships.<ref>Lu, Leah. [https://uproxx.com/music/helena-deland-interview-altogether-unaccompanied-volumes-3-4/\" Canadian Songwriter Helena Deland On The Friendships That Inspire Her Meditative Synth-Pop\"], [[Uproxx]], 17 October 2018. Retrieved on 6 March 2019.</ref>\n\nVol. I & II were released on 2 March and Vol. III & IV were released on 19 October 2018 via Luminelle Recordings and Chivi Chivi.\n\n{{Track listing\n| headline      = Vol. I\n\n|all_writing = Helena Deland\n\n| title_width   = 70%\n| writing_width = \n| music_width   = \n| lyrics_width  =  \n| extra_width   = \n| title1        = There Are a Thousand<ref>Johnson, Tom. [https://www.goldflakepaint.co.uk/new-music-helena-deland-there-are-a-thousand/  \"Helena Deland, There Are a Thousand\"], [[Gold Flake Paint]], 2018. Retrieved on 5 March 2019.</ref>\n| length1       = 3:36\n\n| title2        = Perfect Weather for a Crime<ref>Jett\u00e9, Elise. [https://www.journaldemontreal.com/25-chansons-queb-qui-ont-marque-2018 \"25 chansons queb qui ont marqu\u00e9 2018\"], [[Journal de Montr\u00e9al]], 27 December 2018. Retrieved on 5 March 2019.</ref> \n|length2       = 2:24\n}}\n{{Track listing\n| headline      = Vol. II\n| total_length  = 14:54\n\n| title_width   = 70%\n| writing_width = \n| music_width   = \n| lyrics_width  =  \n| extra_width   =\n\n| title1        = Take It All<ref>MacDonald, Sarah. [https://noisey.vice.com/en_ca/article/a343az/helena-delands-take-it-all-tackles-the-reality-of-romantic-expectations \"Helena Deland's \"Take It All\"], [[Noisey]], 15 February 2018. Retrieved on 5 March 2019.</ref>\n| length1       = 4:36\n\n| title2        = Body Language<ref>Israelsohn, Sophie. [https://www.stereogum.com/1985086/stream-helena-deland-from-the-series-of-songs-altogether-unaccompanied-vol-i-ii/music/album-stream/ \"Stream Helena Deland From The Series Of Songs \"Altogether Unaccompanied\" Vol. I & II\"], [[Stereogum]], 1 March 2018. Retrieved on 5 March 2019.</ref> \n| length2       = 4:18\n}}\n{{Track listing\n| headline      = Vol. III\n\n| title_width   = 70%\n| writing_width = \n| music_width   = \n| lyrics_width  =  \n| extra_width   =\n\n| title1        = Two Queries<ref>Murphy, Sarah. [https://exclaim.ca/music/article/helena_deland_teases_two_new_eps_with_claudion \"Hel