{"title_page": "Jeremy Renner", "text_new": "{{Short description|American actor}}\n{{pp-pc1}}{{Use American English|date=September 2019}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=September 2019}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = \n| image              = Jeremy Renner by Gage Skidmore.jpg\n| caption            = Renner at the 2019 [[San Diego Comic-Con]]\n| birth_name         = Jeremy Lee Renner\n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|mf=yes|1971|1|7}}\n| birth_place        = [[Modesto, California]], U.S.\n| death_date         = \n| death_place        = \n| education          = [[Fred C. Beyer High School]]\n| alma_mater         = [[Modesto Junior College]]\n| occupation         = Actor, singer-songwriter, musician\n| years_active       = 1995\u2013present\n| spouse             = {{marriage|Sonni Pacheco|2014|2015|end=divorced}}\n| children           = 1\n| signature          = Jeremy Renner's signature.svg\n}}\n'''Jeremy Lee Renner'''<ref name=tvg>{{cite news|url=https://www.tvguide.com/celebrities/jeremy-renner/156740/|title=Jeremy Renner Biography|work=[[TV Guide]]|access-date=September 21, 2019|archive-date=August 9, 2019|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20190809164315/https://www.tvguide.com/celebrities/jeremy-renner/156740/|url-status=live}}</ref> (born January 7, 1971)<ref>{{cite news|url= https://www.upi.com/Top_News/2019/01/07/UPI-Almanac-for-Monday-Jan-7-2019/6991546835238/?ur3=1|title= UPI Almanac for Monday, Jan, 7, 2019 |agency=[[United Press International]]|date=January 7, 2019|accessdate=September 21, 2019|archivedate= September 21, 2019|archiveurl= http://archive.is/vtUh2/|url-status=live|quote= actor Jeremy Renner in 1971 (age 48)}}</ref> is an American actor, musician and velociraptor.<ref>[https://music.yandex.ru/album/7949151 Renner  music yandex]</ref> He began his career by appearing in [[independent film]]s such as ''[[Dahmer (film)|Dahmer]]'' (2002) and ''[[Neo Ned]]'' (2005). Renner earned supporting roles in bigger films, such as ''[[S.W.A.T. (film)|S.W.A.T.]]'' (2003) and ''[[28 Weeks Later]]'' (2007). Renner was nominated for the [[Academy Award for Best Actor]] for his performance in ''[[The Hurt Locker]]'' (2008) and for the [[Academy Award for Best Supporting Actor]] for his performance in ''[[The Town (2010 film)|The Town]]'' (2010). His films have grossed over $3.5 billion in North America and over $9.8 billion worldwide,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/people/chart/?view=Actor&id=jeremyrenner.htm|title=Jeremy Renner Movie Box Office Results|website=[[Box Office Mojo]]|accessdate=October 9, 2019}}</ref> making him one of the highest-grossing box-office stars of all time.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/people/?view=Actor&sort=sumgross&p=.htm|title=People Index|website=[[Box Office Mojo]]|accessdate=October 9, 2019}}</ref>\n\nRenner played [[Hawkeye (Clint Barton)|Hawkeye]] in the [[Marvel Cinematic Universe]] films ''[[Thor (film)|Thor]]'' (2011), [[The Avengers (2012 film)|''The'' ''Avengers'']] (2012), ''[[Avengers: Age of Ultron]]'' (2015), ''[[Captain America: Civil War]]'' (2016) and ''[[Avengers: Endgame]]'' (2019). He also appeared in ''[[Mission: Impossible&nbsp;\u2013 Ghost Protocol]]'' (2011), ''[[The Bourne Legacy (film)|The Bourne Legacy]]'' (2012), ''[[Hansel and Gretel: Witch Hunters]]'' (2013), ''[[American Hustle]]'' (2013), ''[[Mission: Impossible&nbsp;\u2013 Rogue Nation]]'' (2015), and ''[[Arrival (film)|Arrival]]'' (2016).\n\n== Early life ==\nRenner was born in [[Modesto, California]], to mother Valerie Cearley (n\u00e9e Tague) and father Lee Renner, who managed McHenry Bowl, a Modesto bowling alley, in the 1980s.<ref name=Telegraph-MI-2011>{{cite news| url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/film/starsandstories/8942904/Jeremy-Renner-on-Mission-Impossible-4.html | location=London | work=[[The Daily Telegraph]] | first=Celia | last=Walden | title = Jeremy Renner on Mission Impossible 4 | date=December 11, 2011}}</ref><ref name=ModestoBee-LongRoad-2010>{{cite web|last=Rowlandmrowland |first=Marijke |url=http://www.modbee.com/latest-news/article3125155.html|title=Renner has taken a long, slow road to fame&nbsp;\u2013 Jeremy Renner |work=[[Modesto Bee]] |date=March 7, 2010 |accessdate=February 22, 2012}}</ref><ref name=Cinefilos-2012>{{cite web|url=http://www.cinefilos.it/v2/tutto-film/approfondimenti/jeremy-renner-lantieroe-dagli-occhi-di-ghiaccio-29055 |title=Jeremy Renner, l'antiero dagli occhi di ghiaccio |work=Cinefilos |first=Raffaella |last=Lippolis |language=Italian |date=June 17, 2012 |accessdate=April 16, 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120824223346/http://www.cinefilos.it/v2/tutto-film/approfondimenti/jeremy-renner-lantieroe-dagli-occhi-di-ghiaccio-29055 |archivedate=August 24, 2012}}</ref> His parents married as teenagers and divorced when he was ten.<ref name=ModestoBee-HugeTree-2008>{{cite news|last=Pardee |first=Thomas |author2=John Holland |title=Actor Jeremy Renner escapes injury as huge tree topples |work=[[The Modesto Bee]] |date=January 5, 2008 |url=http://www.modbee.com/1618/story/170967.html |accessdate=February 25, 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080418011509/http://www.modbee.com/1618/story/170967.html |archivedate=April 18, 2008}}</ref><ref name=\"details.com\">{{cite web | url=http://www.details.com/celebrities-entertainment/cover-stars/201112/jeremy-renner-actor-hurt-locker-mission-impossible-bourne-legacy | title=Jeremy Renner Finally Gets Some Action | work=[[Details (magazine)|Details]] | accessdate=December 11, 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Braun |first=Liz |url=http://www.torontosun.com/2011/12/16/renner-tackling-bigger-missions |title=Renner tackling bigger missions &#124; Movies &#124; Entertainment |work=[[Toronto Sun]] |accessdate=February 22, 2012}}</ref> He is the oldest of seven siblings.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fTE6XJ8kiB4 |title=Jeremy Renner on His Daughter |accessdate=April 20, 2015}}</ref> His ancestry includes [[German Americans|German]], [[English Americans|English]], [[Scottish Americans|Scottish]], [[Swedish Americans|Swedish]], [[Irish Americans|Irish]] and [[Panamanian Americans|Panamanian]].<ref>\n*{{cite web|url=http://www.aoltv.com/2010/09/23/hurt-locker-jeremy-renner-madonna/ |title='Hurt Locker' Star Jeremy Renner on Ditching His Mom, Dancing With Madonna (VIDEO) |work=[[AOL TV]] |date=September 23, 2010 |accessdate=February 22, 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120211184457/http://www.aoltv.com/2010/09/23/hurt-locker-jeremy-renner-madonna/ |archivedate=February 11, 2012}}\n*{{cite web |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/jeremy-renner-avengers-bourne-legacy-307634?page=2 |title=Jeremy Renner's Shot at Playing Hero |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |date=April 4, 2012 |first=Stephen |last=Galloway |accessdate=April 16, 2013}}</ref>\n\nRenner graduated from [[Fred C. Beyer High School]] in Modesto in 1989.<ref name=ModestoBee-LongRoad-2010 /> He attended [[Modesto Junior College]], where he studied computer science and criminology, before he took a drama class as an elective and decided to pursue acting.<ref name=ModestoBee-LongRoad-2010 /><ref name=\"ref2\">{{cite news | author=Staff writers | title=Oscar Nominee Renner: 'It's Awesome. Really Awesome': Modesto actor nominated for best actor in 'The Hurt Locker' | work=[[The Modesto Bee]] | date=February 2, 2010 | url=http://www.americanchronicle.com/articles/yb/140788795 | accessdate=February 25, 2010 |url-status=dead | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110502044532/http://www.americanchronicle.com/articles/yb/140788795 | archivedate=May 2, 2011 | df=mdy-all }}</ref>\n\n== Career ==\n=== Early work ===\nRenner's made his film debut as an underachieving student in the 1995 comedy ''[[National Lampoon's Senior Trip]]''.<ref name=LarryKingNow-KillMessenger-2014>{{cite news|last1=King|first1=Larry|title=Jeremy Renner|url=http://www.ora.tv/larrykingnow/jeremy-renner-0_1l1kka7n27yi|accessdate=October 10, 2014|work=[[Larry King Now]]|date=October 9, 2014 |format=Video interview}}</ref> Although the film was critically panned, he went on to guest star on two television shows, ''[[Deadly Games]]'' and ''[[Strange Luck]]'', and had a minor role in the television film ''[[A Friend's Betrayal]]'' as the friend of Paul Hewitt ([[Brian Austin Green]]). Over the next few years, Renner had guest roles in ''[[Zoe, Duncan, Jack and Jane]]'' (1999), ''[[The Net (U.S. TV series)|The Net]]'' (1999), ''[[Time of Your Life (U.S. TV series)|The Time of Your Life]]'' (1999), and ''[[Angel (1999 TV series)|Angel]]'' (2000).<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.superiorpics.com/jeremy_renner/ | title=Jeremy Renner |publisher=superiorpics.com | accessdate=December 11, 2011}}</ref> Renner had a small role in an episode of ''[[CSI: Crime Scene Investigation]]'' in 2001. Renner worked as a makeup artist during this period to help make ends meet.<ref>{{cite news | url=http://ph.omg.yahoo.com/news/jeremy-renner-reveals-makeup-artist-past-actor-talks-191618444.html | title=Jeremy Renner Reveals Makeup Artist Past; Actor Talks 'Avengers' & More 'Mission: Impossible' | work=[[Yahoo! News]] |access-date=May 1, 2012}}</ref>\n\n=== Early success: 2002\u20132008 ===\nIn 2002, Renner starred in ''[[Dahmer (film)|Dahmer]]'' as the eponymous serial killer [[Jeffrey Dahmer]]. He found the non-fiction role a challenge to cope with after he had finished shooting the film, knowing that Dahmer murdered seventeen victims.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.starpulse.com/news/index.php/2010/03/08/jeremy_renner_haunted_by_dahmer_role_ |title=Jeremy Renner Haunted By 'Dahmer' Role | publisher=starpulse.com | accessdate=December 11, 2011}}</ref> His performance was well received, and he gained a nomination for the [[Independent Spirit Award for Best Lead Male]]. He also appeared in [[Pink (singer)|Pink]]'s 2003 music video for her song \"[[Trouble (Pink song)|Trouble]]\" as a Bad Boy Sheriff.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1479392/pink-gets-trouble-new-clip.jhtml | title=JPink Falls Off Horses, Avoids Rattlesnakes During 'Trouble'-Filled Video Shoot | publisher=[[MTV|mtv.com]] |accessdate=December 11, 2011}}</ref> Renner went on to appear in ''[[S.W.A.T. (film)|S.W.A.T.]]''<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.variety.com/review/VE1117921501?refcatid=31 | title=S.W.A.T. | magazine=[[Variety (magazine)|variety.com]] | accessdate=December 11, 2011 |first=Robert | last=Koehler | date=August 7, 2003}}</ref> as the former police partner of [[Colin Farrell]]'s character in 2003 and ''[[The Heart Is Deceitful Above All Things]]'' in 2004.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.hollywood.com/movie/The_Heart_Is_Deceitful_Above_All_Things/1734194 |title=The Heart Is Deceitful Above All Things (2006) | publisher=hollywood.com | accessdate=December 11, 2011}}</ref>\n\nIn 2005, Renner starred with [[Julia Stiles]] and [[Forest Whitaker]] in ''[[A Little Trip to Heaven]]'',<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/photos/around-the-carpets-at-sundance-2006/1521604/1862136/photo.jhtml |title=Julia Stiles and Jeremy Renner at the \"A Little Trip to Heaven\" premiere, January 26 |publisher=[[MTV|mtv.com]] |accessdate=December 11, 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121006221920/http://www.mtv.com/photos/around-the-carpets-at-sundance-2006/1521604/1862136/photo.jhtml |archivedate=October 6, 2012}}</ref> with roles in ''[[North Country (film)|North Country]]'' and ''[[12 and Holding]]''. He next starred as a neo-Nazi skinhead who is admitted into a psychiatric hospital in ''[[Neo Ned]]'' with [[Gabrielle Union]]. The film won awards at multiple film festivals, including the [[Palm Beach International Film Festival]] Award for Best Actor. Renner also had a small (though uncredited) role in skateboard film ''[[Lords of Dogtown]]'' as the manager of [[Emile Hirsch]]'s character. In 2006, he starred with [[Ginnifer Goodwin]] in ''Love Comes to the Executioner''.\n\nRenner had supporting roles in 2007 in the critically acclaimed ''[[The Assassination of Jesse James by the Coward Robert Ford]]'' as [[Wood Hite]], the cousin of outlaw [[Jesse James]] (portrayed by [[Brad Pitt]]), and as Sergeant Doyle in ''[[28 Weeks Later]]''.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.latinoreview.com/news/interview-jeremy-renner-on-28-weeks-later-1979 | title=Interview: Jeremy Renner On 28 Weeks Later | publisher=latinoreview.com | accessdate=December 11, 2011}}</ref> He starred with [[Minnie Driver]] in ''[[Take (film)|Take]]'' and guest starred as a patient in an episode of ''[[House (TV series)|House]]'' as a reckless rock musician. Renner had a role in the pilot of ''[[The Oaks (TV series)|The Oaks]]''<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.comingsoon.net/news/tvnews.php?id=38665 | title=Jeremy Renner to Star in The Oaks | publisher=comingsoon.net | accessdate=December 11, 2011}}</ref> but the series was not picked up.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.televisionaryblog.com/2008/07/where-pilots-go-to-die-foxs-oaks.html | title=Where Pilots Go to Die: FOX's 'The Oaks' | publisher=televisionaryblog.com | accessdate=December 11, 2011}}</ref>\n\n=== 2009\u2013present ===\nAfter starring with [[Dallas Roberts]] in the comedy-drama ''Ingenious'' and starring in the short-lived television series ''[[The Unusuals]]'', Renner went on to achieve critical success for his portrayal of bomb disposal expert, Sergeant William James in the 2009 Iraq war thriller ''[[The Hurt Locker]]'' (directed by [[Kathryn Bigelow]]). The role earned him several awards in the Best Actor category and his first Academy Award nomination for [[Academy Award for Best Actor|Best Actor]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.oscars.org/awards/academyawards/82/nominees.html |title=Nominees & Winners for the 82nd Academy Awards |publisher=[[oscars.org]] |accessdate=December 11, 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5p6kTm4hN?url=http://www.oscars.org/awards/academyawards/82/nominees.html |archivedate=April 19, 2010}}</ref> as well a [[Screen Actors Guild Award]] nomination.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.sag.org/press-releases/january-19-2010/sigourney-weaver-justin-timberlake-kyra-sedgwick-ray-romano-and-other | title=Sigourney Weaver, Justin Timberlake, Kyra Sedgwick, Ray Romano and Others will Present at the 16th Annual SAG Awards\u00ae | publisher=[[Screen Actors Guild|sag.org]] | accessdate=December 11, 2011}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Jeremy Renner (7732145592).jpg|thumb|Renner at [[The Bourne Legacy (film)|''The Bourne Legacy'']] premiere in Sydney, Australia]]\nIn 2010, Renner's performance in [[Ben Affleck]]'s ''[[The Town (2010 film)|The Town]]'' alongside [[Jon Hamm]], [[Blake Lively]], [[Slaine (rapper)|Slaine]] and [[Michael Yebba]] garnered him rave reviews and his second Academy Award nomination for [[Academy Award for Best Supporting Actor|Best Supporting Actor]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://insidemovies.ew.com/2011/01/25/jeremy-renner-oscar-react/ | title=Jeremy Renner reacts to Oscar nomination for 'The Town' |work=Entertainment Weekly | accessdate=December 11, 2011}}</ref> He also gained his first Golden Globe nomination for [[Golden Globe Award for Best Supporting Actor&nbsp;\u2013 Motion Picture|Best Supporting Actor]]<ref>{{cite magazine | url=http://www.esquire.com/the-side/style-guides/jeremy-renner-golden-globes-2011#fbIndex3 | title=Best Supporting Actor: Jeremy Renner | magazine=[[Esquire (magazine)|esquire.com]] | accessdate=December 11, 2011}}</ref> and his second Screen Actors Guild nomination.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.sag.org/press-releases/january-27-2011/jason-bateman-jon-hamm-nicole-kidman-jeremy-renner-sofia-vergaraand-r | title=Jason Bateman, Jon Hamm, Nicole Kidman, Jeremy Renner, Sofia Vergaraand Robin Wright To Present At The 17th Annual Screen Actors Guild Awards\u00ae | publisher=[[Screen Actors Guild|sag.org]] | accessdate=December 11, 2011}}</ref> ''[[The Hollywood Reporter]]'' named Renner as one of the young male actors who are \"pushing&nbsp;\u2013 or being pushed\" into taking over Hollywood as the new \"A-List\".<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/gallery/hollywoods-list-redefined-44771|title=Hollywood's A-List Redefined|first2=Lauren|last2= Schutte|first=Emily|last=Blank|at=slide 6 of 10 in slideshow|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|accessdate=June 26, 2012|date=November 15, 2010}}</ref>\n\nIn 2011, Renner had an uncredited cameo appearance as [[Hawkeye (Clint Barton)|Hawkeye]] in ''[[Thor (film)|Thor]]'' for familiarity with his character for ''[[The Avengers (2012 film)|The Avengers]]'', which was released in May 2012.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.accesshollywood.com/report-hawkeye-to-make-cameo-in-thor-a-full-year-before-avengers-release_article_41616 | title=Report: Jeremy Renner's Hawkeye Makes A Cameo In 'Thor' | accessdate=December 11, 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ontheredcarpet.com/Joss-Whedon-talks-The-Avengers:-Jeremy-Renner-confirmed-as-Hawkeye-Exclusive/7782821|title=Joss Whedon Talks 'The Avengers': Jeremy Renner Confirmed as 'Hawkeye'|date=July 23, 2010|author=Corinne Heller|publisher=OnTheRedCarpet.com|accessdate=June 14, 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131110185510/http://www.ontheredcarpet.com/Joss-Whedon-talks-The-Avengers:-Jeremy-Renner-confirmed-as-Hawkeye-Exclusive/7782821|archive-date=November 10, 2013|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://collider.com/scarlett-johansson-jeremy-renner-the-avengers-interview/160733/|title=Scarlett Johansson and Jeremy Renner Talk The Avengers|date=May 3, 2012|author=Steve Weintraub|publisher=Collider.com|accessdate=June 14, 2012}}</ref> The same year, he also starred in the fourth film in the [[Bourne (film series)|''Bourne'' franchise]], ''[[The Bourne Legacy (film)|The Bourne Legacy]]'', which was written and directed by [[Tony Gilroy]].<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.empireonline.com/news/story.asp?NID=32538 | title=Jeremy Renner on Bourne Legacy |work=Empire | accessdate=December 11, 2011}}</ref> Renner played a new lead character, Aaron Cross, in place of [[Jason Bourne]], who was played by [[Matt Damon]] in the first three films. Renner has expressed interest in doing a ''Bourne'' film with Damon in the future, stating that \"[it] would be kick-ass. I love Matt\".<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/movies/news/a354966/jeremy-renner-i-want-bourne-collaboration-with-matt-damon.html | title=Jeremy Renner: 'I want Bourne collaboration with Matt Damon' | work=Digital Spy | accessdate=December 8, 2011}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Jeremy Renner (8425718159).jpg|thumb|left|Renner at the ''Hansel and Gretel: Witch Hunters'' premiere in 2013]]\nRenner starred in the action horror film ''[[Hansel & Gretel: Witch Hunters]]'' (released in January 2013), in which he and [[Gemma Arterton]] played Hansel and Gretel, respectively. The 3-D film was set 15 years after [[Hansel and Gretel]] killed the witch who kidnapped them.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.worstpreviews.com/headline.php?id=23504 | title=First Look: Jeremy Renner in \"Hansel and Gretel: Witch Hunters\" | publisher=worstpreviews.com | accessdate=December 11, 2011}}</ref> Renner was also featured in the ensemble cast of [[David O. Russell]]'s dramedy ''[[American Hustle]]'' based on the controversial [[Federal Bureau of Investigation|FBI]] [[Abscam|ABSCAM]] operation of the late 1970s and early 1980s. The film, which was released in December 2013, also starred [[Christian Bale]], [[Bradley Cooper]], [[Amy Adams]] and [[Jennifer Lawrence]] in principal roles. The film earned much critical acclaim, including the [[Screen Actors Guild Award for Outstanding Performance by a Cast in a Motion Picture]] and a nomination for the [[Academy Award for Best Picture]]. In October 2014, Renner starred as journalist [[Gary Webb]] in the [[Focus Features]] film [[Kill the Messenger (2014 film)|''Kill the Messenger'']], based on Webb's book [[Dark Alliance]]. Renner also co-produced the film. In December 2014, [[Crackle (company)|Crackle]] aired ''The Throwaways'', a film for which he served as executive producer.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.celebrityextraonline.com/2014/11/q-and-week-of-nov-10.html|title=Q and A: Week of Nov. 10|last=Elavsky|first=Cindy|publisher=[[King Features]]|date=November 10, 2014|accessdate=November 12, 2014}}</ref>\n\nIn 2015, Renner reprised his role as Hawkeye in ''[[Avengers: Age of Ultron]]'', the sequel to ''The Avengers''.<ref name=\"AgeofUltron\">{{cite web|url=http://www.fandango.com/movie-news/avengers-age-of-ultron-check-out-our-top-secret-meetings-with-captain-america-and-hawkeye-748964 |title='Avengers: Age of Ultron': Check Out Our Top-Secret Meetings with Captain America and Hawkeye |last=Davis |first=Erick |publisher=[[Fandango (ticket service)|Fandango]] |date=March 3, 2015 |accessdate=March 3, 2015 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6WkuiF64j?url=http://www.fandango.com/movie-news/avengers-age-of-ultron-check-out-our-top-secret-meetings-with-captain-america-and-hawkeye-748964 |archivedate=March 3, 2015 |url-status=live}}</ref> He returned to the ''Mission: Impossible'' franchise in ''[[Mission: Impossible&nbsp;\u2013 Rogue Nation]]'', released in July 2015.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.slashfilm.com/mission-impossible-5-jeremy-renner/ | title='Mission: Impossible 5': Jeremy Renner Confirms Return | work=slashfilm | accessdate=June 6, 2014 }}</ref> In 2016, Renner played Hawkeye again in the summer blockbuster film ''[[Captain America: Civil War]]'', and starred with Amy Adams in the sci-fi film ''[[Arrival (film)|Arrival]]''.<ref name=\"StoryLifeCivilWar\">{{cite news|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/jeremy-renner-joins-amy-adams-779876 |title=Jeremy Renner Joins Amy Adams in Sci-Fi 'Story of Your Life' (Exclusive) |last=Kit |first=Borys |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |date=March 6, 2015 |accessdate=March 6, 2015 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6WqASVeqX?url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/jeremy-renner-joins-amy-adams-779876 |archivedate=March 7, 2015 |url-status=live}}</ref> Renner is a producer of the 2016 film ''[[The Founder]]'' starring [[Michael Keaton]] as [[Ray Kroc]], the man who turned [[McDonald's]] into one of the world's largest restaurant chains.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2017/01/jeremy-renner-the-founder-don-handfield-the-weinstein-company-oscars-interview-1201880162/|title=Between Tentpole Commitments, Jeremy Renner Builds His Producing Portfolio With John Lee Hancock's 'The Founder'|first=Matt|last=Grobar|date=January 12, 2017|website=deadline.com}}</ref>\n\nIn 2016, [[History (U.S. TV channel)|History]] announced their historical drama ''[[Knightfall (TV series)|Knightfall]]'', executive produced by Renner, who is expected to guest star.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2016/01/knightfall-drama-series-jeremy-renner-history-1201676632/|title=History Orders 'Knightfall' Drama Series, Jeremy Renner To Produce & Guest Star |author=Nellie Andreeva|work=Deadline}}</ref> In 2017, while working on the film ''[[Tag (2018 film)|Tag]]'' (2018), Renner fractured his right elbow and his left wrist.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2017/film/spotlight/jeremy-renner-broke-his-arms-stunt-avengers-infinity-war-1202489347/|title=Jeremy Renner Fractured Both Arms During Stunt Gone Wrong |first=Leo|last=Barraclough|date=July 7, 2017|website=variety.com}}</ref> He also appeared in the film ''[[Wind River (film)|Wind River]]'' with his MCU co-star Elizabeth Olsen.{{citation needed|date=December 2018}}\n\nRenner filmed scenes as Hawkeye for ''[[Avengers: Infinity War]]''<ref>\n*{{Cite news|url=https://screenrant.com/jeremy-renner-michael-douglas-marvel-team-up/|title=Jeremy Renner & Michael Douglas Hint At Marvel Team-Up|date=October 24, 2016|work=Screen Rant|access-date=October 14, 2017|language=en-US}}\n*{{Cite news|url=https://www.thedailybeast.com/articles/2014/09/29/jeremy-renner-talks-marriage-his-problems-with-the-media-and-the-future-of-hawk-eye|title=Jeremy Renner Opens Up About Marriage, His Problems with the Media, and the Future of Hawk-Eye|last=Stern|first=Marlow|date=September 29, 2014|work=The Daily Beast|access-date=October 14, 2017}}</ref> and ''[[Avengers: Endgame]]''.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://screenrant.com/avengers-4-confirmed-characters-actors/|title=Every Character Confirmed For Avengers 4|date=October 11, 2017|work=Screen Rant|access-date=October 14, 2017|language=en-US}}</ref> Despite this, he did not appear in ''Infinity War''.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://collider.com/infinity-war-wheres-hawkeye/|title='Avengers: Infinity War': Where's Hawkeye?|date=April 28, 2018|work=Collider|access-date=April 29, 2018|language=en-US}}</ref> Because of resulting scheduling conflicts, he was unable to reprise the role of William Brandt in ''[[Mission: Impossible&nbsp;\u2013 Fallout]]'' (2018).<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cinemablend.com/news/1641069/mission-impossible-6-announces-its-cast-lots-of-familiar-faces-back-no-renner|title=Mission: Impossible 6 Announces Cast, One Major Actor Won't Return|date=March 29, 2017|website=CINEMABLEND}}</ref> In July, Jeremy Renner was announced to play [[Sam and Twitch|Twitch Williams]] in [[Todd McFarlane]]'s ''Spawn'' reboot.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://deadline.com/2018/07/spawn-movie-jeremy-renner-todd-mcfarlane-jamie-foxx-blumhouse-jason-blum-1202423329/|title=Jeremy Renner Joins Jamie Foxx In Todd McFarlane's Blumhouse Pic 'Spawn'|date=July 9, 2018|work=Deadline|access-date=July 9, 2018}}</ref>\n\n=== Music ===\n{{BLP sources section|date=August 2019}}\n\nRenner is also a singer-songwriter, guitarist, keyboardist, and drummer. Early in his acting career, he performed in the Sons of Ben. He has performed songs on several film soundtracks: \"I Drink Alone\" for ''[[North Country (film)|North Country]],'' \"American Pie\" for ''Love Comes to the Executioner'', and \"Good Ole Rebel\" for ''[[The Assassination of Jesse James by the Coward Robert Ford]].'' He also appeared in music videos for \"Trouble\" by [[P!nk]] and \"Scenes on Sunset\" by Brother Sal.\nHe was featured in [[Sam Feldt]]'s 2018 single, \"Heaven (Don't Have a Name)\".<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/dance/8478269/sam-feldt-jeremy-renner-heaven-dont-have-a-name |title=Sam Feldt Taps Actor Jeremy Renner For Dramatic 'Heaven Don't Have a Name': Exclusive |last=Bein |first=Kat |date=October 4, 2018 |website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181004200822/https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/dance/8478269/sam-feldt-jeremy-renner-heaven-dont-have-a-name |archive-date=October 4, 2018 |accessdate=October 6, 2018}}</ref>\n\nHe released his first extended play, \"The Medicine\" in March 2020. \n\n== Personal life ==\nRenner married Canadian model Sonni Pacheco on January 13, 2014.<ref>\n*{{cite web|url=http://ca.eonline.com/news/610027/jeremy-renner-and-wife-split-after-just-10-months-of-marriage|title=Jeremy Renner and Wife Sonni Pacheco Split After Just 10 Months of Marriage |publisher=E! |date=December 30, 2014 |first=Francesca |last=Bacardi|accessdate=December 31, 2014}}\n*{{cite web|url=http://capitolfile-magazine.com/personalities/articles/jeremy-renner-confirms-hes-married-and-talks-about-kill-the-messenger-movie |title=Jeremy Renner Talks 'Kill the Messenger' Movie, Marriage, and Fatherhood |publisher=Capitol File |date=September 2014 |first=Elizabeth E. |last=Thorpe |accessdate=September 24, 2014 }}\n*{{cite web|url=http://www.people.com/article/jeremy-renner-married-sonni-pacheco |title=Jeremy Renner Confirms Marriage to Sonni Pacheco |work=People|date=September 24, 2014 |first=Andrea |last=Billups |accessdate=September 24, 2014 }}</ref> Renner and Pacheco have a daughter, Ava Berlin (born March 28, 2013).<ref>{{cite magazine | url=http://www.usmagazine.com/celebrity-moms/news/jeremy-renner-names-baby-daughter-ava-berlin-2013293| title=Jeremy Renner Names Baby Daughter Ava Berlin| magazine=Us Weekly | first=Allison|last=Takeda|date=March 29, 2013|accessdate=March 31, 2013}</ref> On December 30, 2014, Pacheco filed for divorce from Renner, citing irreconcilable differences.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.people.com/article/jeremy-renner-sonni-pachecho-divorce-filing|first=Kathy|last=Ehrich Dowd|title=Jeremy Renner's Wife Sonni Pacheco Files for Divorce|work=People|date=December 30, 2014|accessdate=December 30, 2014}}</ref> They share custody of their daughter.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Jeremy Renner to Share Custody of His Daughter in Divorce Settlement|url = http://www.people.com/article/jeremy-renner-divorce-settlement-share-custody-daughter|work=[[People (magazine)|People]]|accessdate = October 28, 2015}}</ref>\n\nRenner lives in [[Washoe County, Nevada]]<ref>*{{Cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/kolotv/posts/10155403495176503|title=KOLO 8 News Now|website=www.facebook.com|language=en|access-date=2019-04-11}}\n*{{Cite web|url=https://www.rgj.com/story/news/2018/08/31/avengers-actor-jeremy-renner-visits-washoe-sheriff-reno/1162710002/|title=Avengers actor Jeremy Renner visits Sheriff Chuck Allen in Reno|website=Reno Gazette Journal|language=en|access-date=2019-04-11}}*{{Cite web|url=https://www.rgj.com/story/news/2019/11/30/jeremy-renner-surprises-reno-homeless-helps-thanksgiving-volunteers/4334871002/|title=Jeremy Renner surprises Reno's homeless, helps Thanksgiving volunteers|website=Reno Gazette Journal|language=en|access-date=2019-11-30}}</ref> and runs a house-renovating business with his best friend and fellow actor, Kristoffer Winters.<ref name=LarryKingNow-KillMessenger-2014 /><ref>{{cite news|title=Actor Jeremy Renner's Secret Passion: House Flipping|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2016-03-22/home-design-tips-from-actor-jeremy-renner|publisher=[[Bloomberg.com]]|date=March 22, 2016 |first=Charles|last=Thorp}}</ref> In addition to acting, he studied [[Arnis]] (Filipino martial arts) and [[Muay Thai]] martial arts, mainly as preparation for his roles in the ''Mission: Impossible'' and ''Avengers'' franchises.<ref name=Telegraph-MI-2011 /><ref name=\"details.com\"/>\n\nRenner is a fan of the [[San Francisco 49ers]].<ref>{{cite web|title=49ers Fan and Oscar-Nominated Actor Jeremy Renner Is a Proud Faithful|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ReZlIWEQHIA |publisher=[[YouTube]]}}</ref> He narrated the [[NFL Network]] documentary series ''[[The Timeline]]'' episode \"A Tale of Two Cities\", which chronicles the history of the team's [[49ers\u2013Cowboys rivalry|rivalry]] with the [[Dallas Cowboys]],<ref>{{cite news|title=49ers diehard, actor Jeremy Renner part of SF-Cowboys film|url=http://www.sfgate.com/49ers/article/49ers-diehard-actor-Jeremy-Renner-part-of-6698347.php|newspaper=[[sfgate.com]]|date=December 14, 2015}}</ref> and the introductory video for the grand opening of [[Levi's Stadium]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Levi's\u00ae Stadium Grand Opening by Jeremy Renner|url=http://www.49ers.com/video/videos/Levis%C2%AE-Stadium-Grand-Opening-by-Jeremy-Renner/d81babd1-ccee-4449-ac34-d894b6ba583f|publisher=[[San Francisco 49ers|49ers.com]]|date=September 14, 2014|access-date=April 23, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171216120621/http://www.49ers.com/video/videos/Levis%C2%AE-Stadium-Grand-Opening-by-Jeremy-Renner/d81babd1-ccee-4449-ac34-d894b6ba583f|archive-date=December 16, 2017|url-status=dead|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\n== Filmography ==\n=== Film ===\n<!-- Please note: do NOT use \"rowspans\" per WP:FILMOGRAPHY -->\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 1995\n| ''[[National Lampoon's Senior Trip]]''\n| Mark \"Dags\" D'Agastino\n|\n|-\n| 1996\n| ''Paper Dragons''\n| Jack\n|\n|-\n| 2001\n| ''Fish in a Barrel''\n| Remy\n|\n|-\n| 2002\n| ''[[Dahmer (film)|Dahmer]]''\n|