isc.edu/~mnathan/Publications_files/2003_Nathan%2526Petrosino_AERJ_EBS.PDF \n |volume=Winter 2003, Vol. 40, No. 4 \n |pages=905\u2013928 \n |url-status=dead \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150424001834/http://website.education.wisc.edu/~mnathan/Publications_files/2003_Nathan%26Petrosino_AERJ_EBS.PDF \n |archivedate=2015-04-24 \n}}\n* {{Cite journal | doi = 10.1111/j.1467-9566.2005.00466.x | last1 = Nettleton | first1 = S. | last2 = Burrows | first2 = R. | last3 = O'Malley | first3 = L. | year = 2005 | title = The mundane realities of the everyday use of the internet for health, and their consequences for media convergence | url = | journal = Sociology of Health and Illness | volume = 27 | issue = 7| pages = 972\u2013992 | pmid = 16313525 }}\n{{refend}}\n\n==Further reading==\n{{Wiktionary|expert}}{{Wiktionary|expertise}}{{Wikiquote}}\n;Books and publications\n*[http://ssrn.com/abstract=2115768 Scott Fruehwald, The Neurobiology of Learning]\n* [[Ikujiro Nonaka]], [[Georg von Krogh]], and [[Sven Voelpel]], ''Organizational Knowledge Creation Theory: Evolutionary Paths and Future Advances''. Organization Studies, Vol. 27, No. 8, 1179-1208 (2006). SAGE Publications, 2006. DOI 10.1177/0170840606066312\n* {{Cite journal | last1 = Sj\u00f6berg | first1 = Lennart | year = 2001 | title = Limits of Knowledge and the Limited Importance of Trust | url = http://www.dynam-it.com/lennart/attachments/119_limits_of_knwoldge_risk_analysis.pdf | journal = Risk Analysis | pmid = 11332547 | volume = 21 | issue = 1 | pages = 189\u2013198 | doi = 10.1111/0272-4332.211101 | citeseerx = 10.1.1.321.4451 | access-date = 2017-10-24 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20170808203856/http://www.dynam-it.com/lennart/attachments/119_limits_of_knwoldge_risk_analysis.pdf | archive-date = 2017-08-08 | url-status = dead }}\n* {{Cite journal | last1 = Hofer | first1 = Barbara K. | last2 = Pintrich | first2 = Paul R. | year = 1997 | title = The Development of Epistemological Theorie